# MCP Tools: microsoftdocs

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

### microsoft_docs_fetch
Fetch and convert a Microsoft Learn documentation webpage to markdown format.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| url | string | Yes | - | URL of the Microsoft documentation page to read |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "microsoftdocs", toolName: "microsoft_docs_fetch", arguments: { url: "https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-functions/" } })

### microsoft_code_sample_search
Search for code snippets and examples in official Microsoft Learn documentation.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| query | string | Yes | - | Descriptive query, SDK name, method name, or code snippet |
| language | string | No | null | Optional language filter: csharp, javascript, typescript, python, powershell, azurecli, al, sql, java, kusto, cpp, go, rust, ruby, php |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "microsoftdocs", toolName: "microsoft_code_sample_search", arguments: { query: "Azure Functions HTTP trigger", language: "javascript" } })

### microsoft_docs_search
Search official Microsoft/Azure documentation and return up to 10 content chunks.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| query | string | No | null | Query or topic about Microsoft/Azure products, services, or APIs |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "microsoftdocs", toolName: "microsoft_docs_search", arguments: { query: "Azure Functions pricing" } })
